Done. Let me summarize what was done.

The task asked me to fix a blind spot where `state why last-failure` (or any failure ID search) silently hides failures beyond the default 200-event scan window. The error message said "No failure data to diagnose" even when failures exist 201+ events back.

I implemented Option A — a 3-line addition in `handle_why` that appends a windowing hint to the error when:
1. `build_why_report` returns an error (target not found)
2. `limit > 0` (scanning was windowed)
3. `events.len() >= limit` (truncation actually occurred)

The hint reads: "(note: only the most recent {limit} events were scanned; the target may be further back — retry with --limit 0)"

